<br>
&quot;Raven?&quot;, was the only word Yakut could process at this moment. She knew Raven was immortal but her maternal instinct still said 'Fire, not good.' Yakut wrapped her arm around Raven's shoulder, and pulled her into an embrace away from the flames. She did so quickly.<br>
<br>
Yakut didn't pretend to understand, but she tried her best to attempt to understand. Raven and herself had many differences, but many similarities as well. The Queen was confused often about what went on inside her eldest daughter. She had a psychic connection with all her kids, but something kept her from reading into Raven's feelings. Perhaps it was the darkness that Yakut feared, or perhaps it was Raven blocking it her ownself.... <p>-|-Queen Yakut-|-<br>
-Shamaness of the Old Ways-<br>
