<br>
Yakut was right. Darkness was inside of Raven, and a great deal of it. But Raven too withdrew her thoughts from others. <br>
Raven's eyes remained on the fire, and as she sat there in Yakut's arms, completely emotionless on her face, she seemed almost that of a young child . . . begging to emerge. <p><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center">~*~ Jessica ~*~<br>
