<br>
&quot;Ohh..you obviously don't get enough running.  You're heavy as a horse, you old hag!&quot;  She placed her pale, slinder fingers across Yakut's shoulders and attempted to push her off.<br>
<br>
When Yakut was to her feet and offered Amarice help, she had to show some kind of respect...so she took her hand.  When she was to her feet, Amarice brushed off some of the dirt that had managed to collect onto her leathers, and brought her hazel orbs back onto Yakut.<br>
<br>
&quot;Samos...well...it's empty.  It's slightly hard getting a tribe off, which I am sure you know.  I hope you'll be able to drop by again.&quot;<br>
<br>
She eyed Yakut down once more before she brought the shamaness into an embrace.  Amarice lowered her voice and this time as she whispered to Yakut, her voice was full of sincerety instead of sarcasm.<br>
<br>
&quot;I've missed you, Yakut.  I am so glad you've returned.&quot; <p>Ø×××|¯A_m¯a_r¯i_c¯e_&gt;</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3F3F3F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/bamazonsunite.showUserPublicProfile?gid=amznnye>AmznNye</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Visitor</span><br>  Posts: 20<br> <font color=#6F6F6F>(4/26/03 9:25 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm29.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=88.topic&index=53>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Crazy? maybe not....</span><hr size=1> She smiled at Otere's reassurance of her lack of insanity. &quot;I'm glad I came as well...I haven't met very many people since coming to any of the Amazon lands.&quot; She glanced over at the going's on between Yakut and the younger woman, smiling a bit to herself, then looked back to Otere. &quot;Maybe...if you wouldn't mind too much...you could show me around?&quot; She couldn't help the hopeful little glitter that flashed through her blue-green eyes then. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#333333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/bamazonsunite.showUserPublicProfile?gid=otereshamaness>OtereShamaness</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Visitor</span><br>  Posts: 23<br> <font color=#6F6F6F>(4/26/03 11:38 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm29.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=88.topic&index=54>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.members.aol.com/darkmoonhex/images/otere.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Crazy? maybe not....</span><hr size=1> Otere titled her head to the side when Nye spoke a bit of her past.  She loved learning about people's past, and wanted to learn her's.  Her auburn occulars caught a glimpse of the commotion between Yakut and Amarice, a giggled a bit at the two, but quickly returned her attention to Nye when she began to speak again.<br>
